The paper deals with deep convolutional neural networks for image classification, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method involves disentangling appearance and geometric codes, which is a technique used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the vulnerability of deep neural networks to adversarial attacks, which is a topic in computer security (cs.CR).
